Hey, still over here in Jeremiah. üôåüèª Jeremiah is a prophet, called by God to deliver a message, that no one wants to hear. üôÉ He is STILL called to deliver, it regardless of who receives it. His calling is NOT in who receives it, üëâüèª it is only in delivering it. So he‚Äôs feeling weary- understandably so. He is not seeing any tangible fruit, in delivering HIS message. He knows He is called but He doesn‚Äôt see the fruit. Do you ever feel this way? I sure do! This Christian life can feel weary, we are to be set apart, living unto the Lord, by HIS word. Jeremiah is in this hard place, he doesn‚Äôt want to keep going, he is about ready to give up. 

BUT GOD. His word is already in HIS  heart like a fire üî•, a fire shut up in his bones. HE is weary of holding it in; indeed, He cannot.

God‚Äôs word is active + living + a
double edge sword. When we have it in our heart, it‚Äôs impossible to contain it. We indeed can not hold it back!! We need to spend time in the word, studying the word, saturating in the word, üëâüèª so it gets into our hearts. May we get into the word + let it burn into our hearts, so when we are called - even if we are weary- we literally can NOT hold back. üî• 

